{"id":"tense-tn-8","label":"Tenses (TN 8)","lockAfter":3,"list":[{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","commonData":{"title":" Fill in the blanks with appropriate form of the verbs given in the brackets."},"data":["When the burglars broke into the house, everyone *was (is, has been)* (be) sleeping. \nThe milk *was spilt (spilt, had spilt) * (spill) over as she went to see the crowd passing by with loud slogans. \nIf Karthik *doesn't make (don't make, hasn't make)* (not + make) any mistake, he will be rewarded. \nThey were watching TV when they *heard (have heard) * (hear) a loud bang at the door. \nThe bus *had left (has left, left)* (leave) the stop before we could catch it. ","Arya *has been playing (has played, has playing)* (play) the same song for last three days. It has become boring now. \nManju *will call (calls)* (call) after she reached home. \nThe show *will have completed (will complete)* (complete) its one thousand episodes by next month. \nDon’t worry, we will be *reaching (reach)* (reach) the airport in time. \nPrasanna has *fallen (fell)* (fall) sick after eating some snacks on the road side shop. "]},{"label":"Multiple Choice Questions","type":"mcq","id":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Choose the correct option to complete the sentences."},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"The climate of the city _____ mild and pleasant most of the time.","options":"remains, is remaining,  was remaining, is remained"},{"qText":"He _____ a hotel in Ooty, a beautiful city in Tamilnadu.","options":"booked, booking, was booking, had booked"},{"qText":"You will certainly _____ rewards for what you are doing.","options":" be getting, get,  had got,  was getting"},{"qText":"Do you _____ the day we moved the piano upstairs?","options":"remember, remembered, are remembering , had remembered"},{"qText":"The rain completely ____ our day","options":"spoilt, is spoiling, is spoilt,  was spoilt "}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Akbar ____ the king at the age of fifteen after the sudden death of his father.","options":"became, was becoming, had become, become"},{"qText":"The criminal ____ the place before the police could reach.","options":" had escaped,  was escaping, is escaping, will escape"},{"qText":"They _____ all the arrangements before the guest's arrival.","options":"will have made , will be made, had been making, were making"},{"qText":"Sabithra _____ her job by tomorrow evening.","options":"will have completed, will complete, will be completing,  will have been completing"},{"qText":"Harshini _____ her mother in making rangoli in the yard for the last one hour.","options":"has been helping,  is helping,  has helped, helps"}]}]},{"id":"fillup-2","label":"Fill up:  Conditional Sentences","type":"fillup","data":{"title":" Complete the Conditional Sentences. Decide whether to use Type I, II or III.","text":"If I had time, I *would go (will go)* (go) shopping with you.\n            If you *speak (can speak, will speak)* (speak) English, you will get along with them perfectly.\n            If they had gone for a walk, they *would have turned (might turned)* (turn) the lights off.\n            If she *comes (come, can come)* (come) with us, we will go to the zoo.\n             I would have told you, if I *had seen (have seen)* (see) him."}},{"label":"Choose the best answer.","type":"mcq","id":"mcq-2","data":{"title":"Choose the best answer.","questions":[{"qText":"I will come if I _____ time","options":"have, had,  will have"},{"qText":"If he is late, we _____ without him.","options":"will start, would start, would have started"},{"qText":"If you ______ me, I would tell you.","options":"asked, had asked,  will ask"},{"qText":"Will it be all right if I _____ a friend tonight?","options":"bring, brought, had brought"},{"qText":"If you _____ to learn a musical instrument, you have to practice.","options":"want, wanted, wants"}]}},{"id":"match","label":"Match the following","type":"match","data":{"title":"Match the following.","text":"If they worked hard, they would win.\n         If I invite Shalini, she will come to our party.\n         If I had got enough money, I would have bought these shoes."}},{"id":"fillup-3","label":"Fill up:  Conditional Sentences - 2","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks with correct verb forms.","text":"If you *go (gone)* out with your friends tonight, I *will watch (would watch, have watched)* the football match on TV.\n          If he *tried (tries)* harder, he *would reach( had reached)* his goals.\n          If we *listen (had listen)* to the radio, we *will hear (heard)* the news."}}]}